accessibility.text: There’s nothing in those documentation telling you about configuring for login and all. Configuring Varnish Cache is not in this presentation. I mean, I used to have to dig through the net to look for compatible configurations.
That said, I’ll prepare a special presentation about Varnish Cache, and some samples too.
In the mean time, avoid using it, unless you feeling lucky and adventurous. Look at next slide to see how the diagram change, and it is not a lot. Maybe just the performance part.
